definition.value: A major geometrical isomer of roxithromycin.
The (25R)-diastereomer of 3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-al.
The (25S)-diastereomer of 3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-al.
A branched-chain saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of isovaleric acid; reported to improve ruminal fermentation and feed digestion in cattle.
A member of the class of propanals that is propanal substituted by a methyl group at position 2.
A branched, short-chain, saturated fatty acid anion; the conjugate base of isobutyric acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A primary alcohol that is  isopentane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1.
Antibiotic isolated from Streptomyces clavuligerus. It acts as a suicide inhibitor of bacterial beta-lactamase enzymes.
A 2,4-diaminobutyric acid that has S-configuration.
The parent compound of the cyclohexenones, composed of cyclohexanone having one double bond in the ring.
Any six-membered alicyclic ketone having one double bond in the ring.
A 5-O-phosphono-D-ribofuranosyl diphosphate with a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
Compounds containing single -N=N- group.
A fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (2E,4E)-deca-2,4-dienoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.
Any  azo compound containing two -N=N- groups.
The trans-isomer of chalcone.
The cis-stereoisomer of chalcone.
A 2',3,4,4',6'-pentahydroxychalcone with a trans configuration.
The (2S,3S)-diastereomer of 2,3-dihydroxy-2,3-dihydrobenzoic acid.
A member of the class of 3-nitroanisoles that is anisole in which one of the hydrogens meta to the methoxy group is replaced by a nitro group.
A substituted aniline that is 3-nitroanisole in which the hydrogen para to the methoxy group is replaced by an amino group.
Any member of the class of mononitroanisoles in which the nitro group is situated meta to the methoxy group.
Any member of the class of mononitroanisoles in which the nitro group is situated para to the methoxy group.
An acyl sulfate where the acyl group is specified as acetyl.
A monohydroxyquinoline carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 7.
A monohydroxyquinoline that is quinoline substituted by a hydroxy group at position 8. Its fungicidal properties are used for the control of grey mould on vines and tomatoes.
Any member of the class of quinolines carrying at least one methyl substituent.
A methylquinoline carrying a methyl substituent at position 4.
